						<summary>

						<p>Base of a sculpture in a shrine near the ruined Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>MANMATHA.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated in the cyclic year Manmatha, Śrāvaṇa śu. 15. It refers to a certain Āvumma, wife of Vēlvula Basvireḍi, who became <hi rend="italic">pēraṅṭālu</hi> (<hi rend="italic">i.e.,</hi> committed <hi rend="italic">sati</hi>).</p>						

